{
  "ecology": "As an engineered entity, the Blood Knight possesses no natural habitat or diet, instead serving as a dedicated, tireless sentinel in fortified strongholds or necromantic war zones. It operates entirely under the command of its dark master, usually acting alone or in small, terrifying contingents to guard key artifacts or command undead armies. Its 'feeding' cycle is metaphorical, as it requires the life force drained through combat to fuel its bloodsteel core and maintain its maximum power.",
  "lore": "Blood Knights are grim fusion golems created by powerful necromancers or blood mages, often involving the sacrifice of a loyal but disgraced knight whose soul is bound to the bloodsteel armor. The armor itself is forged in a ritual using the blood of numerous victims, giving it its dark red sheen and potent necrotic properties. They are prized for their exceptional loyalty, resilience, and unique ability to resist common tactics that defeat either constructs or undead alone.",
